@startuml access_auth_to_rear_door_unlock_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Access Auth To Rear Door Unlock Signal Flow\n(door control + key auth -> DOOR_RL lock-state enforcement)

participant "Door control / key auth /\ndrive context" as AccessCtx #F4F7FB
participant "DOOR_RL\nrear-left door owner" as DoorRL #E8F7E8
participant "Rear door state bus" as DoorBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Rear Door Inputs ==

AccessCtx -> DoorRL : gDoorControlCmd / gChildLockCmd\ngKeyPresence / gDkeyAccessState\ngImmobilizerState / gKeyAuthState\ndriveState
DoorRL -> DoorRL : if driveState == 0 and key auth is valid\nthen accessAuthorized = 1
DoorRL -> DoorRL : unlockRequest = (gDoorControlCmd > 0)
DoorRL -> DoorRL : childLockActive = (gChildLockCmd > 0)
note right of DoorRL
Representative gating inputs
- DoorControlCmd
- ChildLockCmd
- key access / immobilizer auth
- driveState
end note

== Lock-state Publish ==

DoorRL -> DoorRL : if accessAuthorized and unlockRequest and childLockActive == 0\nthen lockState = 0 else lockState = 1
DoorRL -> DoorBus : frmDoorStateMsg\nDoorRlLockState / DoorRlOpenState / DoorRlWindowPos
note right of DoorRL
Representative outputs
- DoorRlLockState
- DoorRlOpenState
- DoorRlWindowPos
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

DoorBus -> Obs : rear-door lock/open readback

note over AccessCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Access authorization and door command reach DOOR_RL
2. DOOR_RL checks drive-state and child-lock constraints
3. Rear-left door lock state is enforced and published
4. Panels show whether rear-door unlock was permitted
end note

@enduml
